TEXT PROPERTIES:
1. Color
1. Color: colorname

2. Hexadecimal values (0-9, A-F)
 eg color: #FFFFFF;
 color #FFFFFF : White
      #000000: Black
      #FF0000: Red

shorthand for white = #FFF
              red = #F00
using shorthand not recommended

3. rgb color code (0-256):
eg - color: rgb(255, 0, 0); - red

4.rgba color code (0-256):
eg color: rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.6)

2. text-align (left, right, center, justify):
justify: aligning text according to its length

3.text-transform(uppercase, lowercase, capitalize):
Capitalize only uses uppercase for initials

4.text-decoration(overline, underline, line-through):

5. text-indent(px):
eg. text-indent: 5px

6. letter-spacing(px): Kerning

7. word-spacing(px): Space between two words

8.line-height(px): space between two lines

FONT PROPERTIES:

1. font-size(px/em):
eg/ font-size: 14px or 1em
em is responsive

2. font-family():
    e.g. font-family: Arial, Times new Roman
    The first available will be applied if neither available machines default font is used.

3. font-weight(bold, normal, 100, 200...700, bolder):
  default is normal, bold and normal available on machines

4. font-style(normal, italic):
  default normal.

DIV:
background-color: red
background-image: url("path")
background-repeat: no-repeat;
                  repeat-x;
                  repeat-y;
                  repeat-all;

background: red url("path") no-repeat;
color will be applied behind the image. Image will always be over the color;

BORDER:
1. border-color:
2. border-width(px):
3. border-style(solid, dashed, dotted, inset, outset):
4. border-left
5. border-top
6  border-bottom
7. border-right
  eg border-left-color/ border-left-width
     border-left: 1px solid blue;

MARGIN:
margin(px):
eg margin: 10px (from all sides)
   margin: 10px(top, bottom) 20px(left, right)
   margin: 10px(top) 20px (left, right) 10px(bottom)
   margin: 10px(top) 20px(right) 30px(bottom) 40px(left)
   margin-left:10px
   margin: (0, auto) to center a div

padding: similar to margin

DISPLAY
display(none, block, inline,):
none will hide it

visibility(hidden, visible):

opacity(0-1):

float(left, right, none):
none is default.

position(absolute, relative, static, fixed): To be avoided
static is default

absolute: will work according to the closest relative parent with body being the farthest relative parent.
relative: will work according to the relative parent. It will have scrollbars is the top/left position exceed the width and height of the parent.
fixed:
